column5: Well the ice is in great shape 8 to 10" now running sleds and atvs on the ice ...this might be my last report unless we loose ice walleye are here and on the bite ...not many guys fishing this winter been quite out there by myself lol... here is a fish from this morning 8:30am and also lots a hog ...
Thx for the report Steve. I will be down that was at least once this winter for smelts. You have any in your marina ?

Nice report thanks fishmaster. I've been to Dunville many time to vist family but never fished the big lake.  Can you steer me in a general direction of where your fishing? I'm heading down on Saturday for a birthday.  Question for you what's the story with the big catfish mount?  My email address is [emailÂ protected]  Thanks Tom
Were going sun morn..Got a hut booked..so stoked for this one!!! will post a report when we catch fish!....
Yes the smelts are in the Marina ...
Stop in we will send ya in the right direction ...google my name for directions ..
Thanks for the report Steve.  I go for the walleye but I can't resist the smelt. One good feed a year, works for me!  Dan O.
